<body>
  <header>
    <h1>THE CAMPAIGN</h1>
    <p>Creating a [Successful] Campaign Is Part Art, Part Science, All Magic</p>
  </header>

  <section>
    <h2>About the Show</h2>
    <p>The Campaign is a unique unscripted competition series combining startup acceleration, content creation, and influencer marketing. It supports early-stage minority startups by pairing them with content creators to develop viral campaigns and gain digital traction.</p>
  </section>

  <section>
    <h2>The Problem</h2>
    <div class="cards">
      <div class="card">Brands struggle with influencer integration—ROI, pricing, and creative control.</div>
      <div class="card">Black creators are underpaid despite producing high-performing content.</div>
      <div class="card">Minority founders lack access to early users and creative marketing tools.</div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <section>
    <h2>The Solution</h2>
    <p>Startups and creators collaborate to build viral campaigns. Startups gain visibility and funding; creators gain equity and career growth—everyone wins.</p>
  </section>

  <section>
    <h2>Value Proposition</h2>
    <div class="value-box">
      The Campaign empowers minority-owned startups and underrepresented creators to co-create compelling content for digital-first audiences, amplifying authentic voices in the creator economy.
    </div>
  </section>

  <section>
    <h2>Market Opportunity</h2>
    <ul>
      <li>Creator economy projected to reach $480B by 2027</li>
      <li>Authenticity and diversity are driving brand engagement</li>
      <li>Creators are launching top-selling brands (Feastables, Prime, Huda Beauty)</li>
    </ul>
  </section>

  <section>
    <h2>Growth Strategy</h2>
    <ol>
      <li>Year 1: Launch pilot with 4 startups</li>
      <li>Year 2–3: Scale, improve production, add brand partners</li>
      <li>Year 4+: License format, launch spinoffs, attract distributors</li>
    </ol>
  </section>

  <section>
    <h2>Financial Outlook</h2>
    <p>Projected revenue: Up to $15M by Year 6 via licensing, partnerships, and branded spinoffs.</p>
    <p>Inspired by the $80M exit of Hot Ones.</p>
  </section>

  <section>
    <h2>About Us</h2>
    <p>Dope Original Co. is a culturally driven media company creating immersive, cross-platform content. Our flagship series, Bodega Talks, amassed over 60M views. We’re committed to storytelling that elevates culture, equity, and Gen Z voices.</p>
  </section>

